id: jf-mkzh
title: Enforce 100 percent repository-wide test coverage
description: "Replace the legacy 59 percent command-layer ratchet with a mandatory, non-bypassable 100 percent threshold for statements, branches, functions, and lines across every source file. Coverage must come from meaningful unit, integration, functional, acceptance, smoke, dogfood, performance, white-box, black-box, and read-only live E2E tests; exclusions and artificial execution-only tests are not acceptable."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 0
tags[5]: active-ratchet,coverage,quality,roadmap,testing
created_at: "2026-07-16T17:00:03.971Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T05:14:21.420Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 1440
acceptance_criteria: "Statements, branches, functions, and lines each measure exactly 100 percent across all source code; Coverage thresholds are enforced globally and per-file in every release and pull-request gate; Tests assert observable behavior and failure paths without coverage-only no-op execution or duplicated cases; Read-only live E2E, packaged-binary smoke, acceptance, performance, and dogfood suites are mandatory documented gates; Coverage cannot be reduced through ignore directives, source exclusions, or threshold changes without explicit governance failure"
goal: jf-mqpo
value: "Make every shipped behavior and failure path executable, reviewable, and regression-proof."
impact: Eliminates the current untested command-callback surface and prevents future uncovered production code.
outcome: A genuine 100/100/100/100 coverage contract enforced repository-wide.
why_now: Measured baseline is 44.93 percent functions and 58.83 percent lines; the user has elevated full coverage to the highest-priority release requirement.
parent: jf-gn5j
risk: critical
confidence: high
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
