comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:16:04.867Z",codex-jellyfin,Highest-priority requirement accepted. Current Bun coverage reports only functions and lines; evaluating LCOV/four-dimension enforcement and coverage capture for command subprocesses before selecting the non-cheatable gate.
  "2026-07-21T19:52:49.060Z",codex-jellyfin,Coverage remains the principal release blocker. Bun coverage reports 58.83% lines and 44.93% functions; Vitest can express all four 100% thresholds but its Node runtime currently fails 254 tests across 14 Bun-specific suites using Bun.spawn or Bun.serve. No artificial exclusions or mocked coverage inflation will be accepted.
  "2026-07-21T20:04:29.442Z",codex-jellyfin,"Latest post-change coverage run: 901 pass, 177 live-only skips, 0 fail; 58.64% lines and 44.56% functions. Command callbacks execute primarily in subprocess acceptance tests and are not attributed to the parent Bun coverage profile, which is the dominant instrumentation gap."
  "2026-07-22T04:41:08.659Z",codex-jellyfin,"Continuing implementation on 2026-07-22 after full all-status inventory; will measure current exact coverage first, close meaningful gaps, and verify read-only installed-binary E2E against the private configured instance."
  "2026-07-22T04:50:16.913Z",codex-jellyfin,"Portability foundation completed: typed Node adapters make 894 deterministic tests pass under Vitest; authoritative four-metric baseline is 38.19 statements, 37.40 branches, 49.92 functions, 37.87 lines. Live compiled CLI read-only suite passed 177/177. Item remains in progress because genuine 100/100/100/100 is not met."
  "2026-07-23T04:51:19.423Z",codex-jellyfin,"2026-07-23 continuation: full all-status PM lineage, live GitHub state, official Jellyfin sources, and private-profile boundaries reviewed. Measuring exact current four-metric gaps before adding behavior-focused tests; no exclusions or threshold weakening."
  "2026-07-23T05:14:21.420Z",codex-jellyfin,"2026-07-23 diagnostic after official TOON work: portable Vitest gate passes 906/906 with 38.24% statements, 37.38% branches, 50.00% functions, and 37.90% lines. The 100/100/100/100 acceptance requirement remains open and is not claimed complete."
notes[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T17:00:03.971Z",codex,"Baseline from bun test --coverage on 2026-07-16: 888 pass,177 credential-dependent E2E skip,44.69% functions,59.26% lines; changed session formatter 100% functions and lines."
  "2026-07-21T19:13:34.272Z",codex-jellyfin,"Baseline measured with bun test --coverage on 2026-07-21: 898 pass, 177 skipped, 0 fail; 44.93% functions and 58.83% lines. Bun's text reporter exposes only functions/lines, so the mandatory gate must use a four-dimension instrumenter and per-file thresholds while preserving Bun compatibility."
  "2026-07-21T19:52:50.098Z",codex-jellyfin,"Decision: retain this feature in progress until genuine 100/100/100/100 source coverage is demonstrated. The next implementation step is a runtime-neutral test process/server harness plus exact branch inventory, not threshold weakening."
  "2026-07-22T04:41:09.309Z",codex-jellyfin,"Quality rule: coverage work must assert observable behavior and failure paths; no ignore directives, artificial execution-only cases, or duplicated tests."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T20:04:30.337Z",codex-jellyfin,"Bun 1.3.11 exposes text and LCOV reporters but only native line/function threshold dimensions; Vitest exposes four dimensions but does not merge Bun child-process coverage automatically. Reaching the governed target requires in-process command execution or an explicit child-profile merge, followed by real missing-branch tests."
  "2026-07-22T04:50:17.571Z",codex-jellyfin,Bun subprocess acceptance tests provide strong black-box behavior proof but child execution is not attributed to parent coverage. Keep them mandatory and separate; use typed Node-compatible harnesses plus in-process command tests for deterministic four-metric attribution.
